    "text_1": {
      "type": "text",
      "id": "text_1",
      "source_id": null,
      "content": "Today we relaunch Substance.io as an effort to put more emphasis on Substance as a platform. With Substance, we would like to contribute an extensive content creation and annotation framework built on web infrastructure. It is designed to be customized and integrated into existing workflows."
    },
    "text_2": {
      "type": "text",
      "id": "text_2",
      "source_id": null,
      "content": "Since 2010, we managed to solve many of the core problems associated with browser-based document manipulation. To date Substance provides:"
    },
    "text_3": {
      "type": "text",
      "id": "text_3",
      "source_id": null,
      "content": "A JSON-based document model, that can be customized (Substance.Document)"
    },
    "text_4": {
      "type": "text",
      "id": "text_4",
      "source_id": null,
      "content": "Support for incremental changes (Substance.Operator)"
    },
    "text_5": {
      "type": "text",
      "id": "text_5",
      "source_id": null,
      "content": "Versioning (Substance.Chronicle)"
    },
    "text_6": {
      "type": "text",
      "id": "text_6",
      "source_id": null,
      "content": "A building block for displaying and editing documents (Substance.Surface)"
    },
    "text_7": {
      "type": "text",
      "id": "text_7",
      "source_id": null,
      "content": "A plugin system for customized content types (Substance.Nodes)"
    },
    "list_1": {
      "type": "list",
      "id": "list_1",
      "source_id": "",
      "items": [
        "text_3",
        "text_4",
        "text_5",
        "text_6",
        "text_7"
      ],
      "ordered": false
    },
    "text_8": {
      "type": "text",
      "id": "text_8",
      "source_id": null,
      "content": "Please have a look at the official Manual to learn more about the individual modules. For a general introduction see here."
    },
    "header_1": {
      "type": "heading",
      "id": "header_1",
      "source_id": "substance-io",
      "content": "Substance IO",
      "level": 2
    },
    "text_9": {
      "type": "text",
      "id": "text_9",
      "source_id": null,
      "content": "The new Substance.io is powered by our new minimal publishing system, IO. It lets you write your article in Markdown and define figures, tables etc. in a simple JSON syntax. All that input is compiled into a full-fledged Substance Article including the main content, meta information like the title and authors and figures you have specified. It works similarly to Jekyll, a static site generator written in Ruby. Compiled IO document repositories can be hosted on any webserver. It's only a bunch of static files."
    },
    "header_2": {
      "type": "heading",
      "id": "header_2",
      "source_id": "substance-in-the-wild",
      "content": "Substance in the wild",
      "level": 2
    },
    "text_10": {
      "type": "text",
      "id": "text_10",
      "source_id": null,
      "content": "A platform is only a platform if applications built on top of it. We are happy that there's a production-ready Substance app out there. And there are more to come."
    },
    "header_3": {
      "type": "heading",
      "id": "header_3",
      "source_id": "elife-lens",
      "content": "eLife Lens",
      "level": 3
    },
    "figure_1": {
      "type": "figure",
      "id": "figure_1",
      "url": "http://backbonejs.org/docs/images/lens.png",
      "label": "",
      "caption": null
    },
    "text_11": {
      "type": "text",
      "id": "text_11",
      "source_id": null,
      "content": "In collaboration with Open Access publisher eLife we developed a new way to display scientific content, eLife Lens. This tool is built on top of the Substance technology stack and has been successfully integrated by eLife and Landes Bioscience."
    },
    "header_4": {
      "type": "heading",
      "id": "header_4",
      "source_id": "fidus-writer",
      "content": "Fidus Writer",
      "level": 3
    },
    "text_12": {
      "type": "text",
      "id": "text_12",
      "source_id": null,
      "content": "We're teaming up with the guys behind Fidus Writer. They already have a working solution for editing scientific documents in the browser. Together we'll be building version 2.0, using the Substance technology stack, allowing incremental updates, versioning and replication for collaborative workflows."
    },
